1. Phishing
Definition

Phishing is a cyber attack in which attackers trick users into revealing passwords, OTPs or banking information through fake emails or websites.

Real World Example

In 2020, attackers sent fake emails pretending to be trusted companies to steal user credentials.

Prevention
Check email sender.
Never click suspicious links.
Enable MFA.
Verify websites before login.
2. Malware
Definition

Malware is malicious software designed to damage or gain unauthorized access to systems.

Examples:

Virus
Worm
Trojan
Spyware
Real World Example

The ILOVEYOU worm infected millions of computers worldwide.

Prevention
Use antivirus.
Avoid unknown downloads.
Update software regularly.
3. Ransomware
Definition

Ransomware encrypts files and demands money to restore access.

Real World Example

The WannaCry attack infected more than 200,000 computers worldwide.

Prevention
Keep backups.
Update systems.
Avoid suspicious attachments.
4. Social Engineering
Definition

Social engineering manipulates people into revealing confidential information.

Example

An attacker pretends to be IT support and asks for passwords.

Prevention
Verify identities.
Never share passwords.
Be cautious of urgent requests.
5. Data Breach
Definition

A data breach occurs when unauthorized individuals gain access to sensitive information.

Example

The Yahoo Data Breach exposed billions of user accounts.

Prevention
Use strong passwords.
Enable MFA.
Monitor accounts regularly.
